e) line intersects the red segment.\nb) If you run the same command \"fd ...\" twice, where will the avatar go?\nc) Can you describe a way according to which the avatar would go up successively starting from the bottom edge of the red segment, to the intersect points points formed by the red segment and the 5th, 4th, 3rd, 2nd and the 1st line?\nd) Test if your method on c) can be used in other cases, such as:\n\n              «riddle 125 38 20»\n              «riddle 140 45 20»\n              «riddle 150 48 20»\n\nor other cases you can try yourself, when the red segment has its edges on the 1st and the 6th line. (You can use the variation tool for its correct placement).\ne) Can you compose a conjecture for the intersect points, where the horizontal lines intersect the red one?\nTry to prove it.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n TIP\n-------------------\ne) The horizontal lines divide the red segment into 5 equal segments.\n\n\n\n\n","sliders":{},"objects":[]}